peace of mind with Osmosis so you can focus on doing your
best","text":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e⇨ Is Osmosis right for my
specialty?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAnybody pursuing a career in
medicine, nursing, or health care can benefit from Osmosis. From MDs and DOs
to PAs, RNs, NPs, and other health professionals, (even patients) use our
platform to learn and prepare for classroom lectures, clinical rotations,
boards, and exams. We specialize in transforming complex health topics into
easy-to-understand videos, and offer unique study tools that support you
throughout your journey; from day one to patient one and
beyond!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e⇨ Is Osmosis
expensive?\u0026nbsp;\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFor the price of a
textbook or two, Osmosis prepares you for learning success throughout your
learning
journey.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eChoose
the plan length that works with your budget (the longer you subscribe, the
more you save) and you can cancel anytime. With the addition of the new
Clinical Sciences library, we also have content that meets specific learning
paths for a variety of specialties and
disciplines.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eDid
you know that we also provide group discounts to eligible learners? Get a
group of your classmates together, reach out, and we’ll see what kind of
discount we can
offer!\u0026nbsp;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e⇨ Can I trust
the material?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWith 100+ subject-matter experts
and content creators on staff and serving on our curriculum advisory boards,
all of our content is rigorously developed and reviewed to ensure you get the
best, most up-to-date information possible. We even provide content that
qualifies for continuing education (CME/CE)
credits.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWith
the addition of the Clinical Sciences library, we now offer content aligned to
US core clerkship curriculum guidelines to support you throughout your entire
health care learning journey. All of our Clinical Sciences content is created
in partnership with active clerkship directors and developed, written, and
reviewed by qualified senior clinicians who expertly scope Osmosis content for
first-time clinical
learners.\u003cbr\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e⇨
I want more information. Who can I
contact?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe’re here for you. Email us at
support@osmosis.org or click on the blue bubble on the bottom right corner of
your screen to chat with one of our team
members.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e","alignment":"left","width":"full","cta":{"buttonColor":"primaryLightest","tracking":{"type":"generic"},"caption":"Read
